HEADWORD: Astrakhan
<hw>As`tra*khan"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to <geog>Astrakhan</geog> in <country>Russia</country> or its
products; made of an Astrakhan skin.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos>
<def>The skin of stillborn or young lambs of that region, the curled
wool of which resembles fur.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

